## Edge cases

- **Multilingual code-switching** (e.g., Thai-accented English with Thai phrases mid-sentence):
  XTTSv2 handles it natively; fine-tuned StyleTTS2 requires per-utterance language tags
  and a code-switched dataset. Flag this to the user; do not silently assume.
- **License conflict:** user said "commercial deployment" but the recommended backbone
  is research-only (F5-TTS, some Coqui checkpoints). Refuse to write ARCHITECTURE.md
  with that pairing — explicitly say "license posture and quality tier conflict; pick
  the next-best license-compatible model OR change the deployment intent."
- **Latency budget physically impossible:** user wants 100ms streaming on CPU-only
  with diffusion-style StyleTTS2. Surface the conflict. Recommend Piper or a
  distilled VITS instead.
- **"Just clone my voice" mid-skill:** stop and route to `/voice-clone` — that skill
  has consent + watermark guardrails this skill does not.
- **Existing baseline outperforms recommendation:** ask the user to confirm via
  `/benchmark-models` or `/voice-eval` before scrapping. Architecture switches are
  weeks of work.
- **Hall's TSL → fingerspelling case:** Thai-accented English with teaching-cadence
  prosody. Recommend fine-tuned StyleTTS2 + `/prosody-control` for the cadence
  surface. Cite this case in the plan.

